After the analysis of Nesbitt and his colleagues, Tawa hallae is an original Theropode.
It has an interesting combination of primitive and advanced properties, says Nesbitt.
At the skull of Tawa hallae, for example, the researchers found clues on airbags, such as they also own the descendants of the Theropods, the birds.
Thanks to the airbags, the bird’s breathing is more efficient than that of mammals.
At Tawa hallae, the bones of the spine were apparently partly filled with air.
Tawa is the oldest and most primitive theropod with air bags, Randall Irmis says.
Since the related line of the huge sauropods later also had air bags and lightweight buttons, the common ancestor of both groups likely had already produced this useful innovation.
At least three migration waves to North America
Because the most primitive dinosaurs had lived in South America so far, the researchers followed that the ochres appeared there for the first time.
