Cost advance of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audex ensures that the user receives a cost advance in just four steps: identifying the vehicle, searching the spare part, creating and creating a cost advance.
The easy handling of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially in order to convince the older professionals who are usually more or less opposed to the use of these new computer techniques.
The database comprises 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger vehicles, 109 land cars, 137 motorcycles, 78 small transporters and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with internet connection for use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified by means of the driving frame number, a graphic of the respective model appears and after that the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables, such as the price for work hours, uptimes or discounts, and after that he can print the cost advance and pass it on to his customers.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for assessment such as AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalog.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workplace-oriented does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of use for this tool is 350 euros a year, a amount that the customer can pay without further charge.
